# ============================================================================
# GITIGNORE - ft_transcendence
# ============================================================================
#
# WHAT IS THIS FILE?
# ------------------
# Tells Git which files to IGNORE (not track).
# These files won't be committed to your repository.
#
# WHY IGNORE FILES?
# -----------------
# 1. Security: Don't commit secrets (.env files)
# 2. Size: Don't commit huge folders (node_modules)
# 3. Reproducibility: Don't commit generated files (build/)
# 4. Cleanliness: Don't commit editor junk (.vscode settings)
#
# SYNTAX:
# -------
# file.txt      → Ignore file.txt in any directory
# /file.txt     → Ignore file.txt in root only
# folder/       → Ignore entire folder
# *.log         → Ignore all .log files
# !important.log → DON'T ignore this specific file
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# DEPENDENCIES
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: External packages installed by npm
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - HUGE folder (hundreds of MB)
#   - Recreatable with "npm install"
#   - Different per OS (native modules)
#
# IF YOU DON'T IGNORE: Repository becomes massive, slow to clone
# ============================================================================
node_modules/

# ============================================================================
# BUILD OUTPUT
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Compiled/generated code
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Recreatable with "npm run build"
#   - Different per environment
#   - Can cause merge conflicts
#
# build/         → SvelteKit production build
# .svelte-kit/   → SvelteKit development cache
# ============================================================================
build/
.svelte-kit/

# ============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT FILES - ⚠️ CRITICAL SECURITY ⚠️
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Files containing secrets and configuration
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Contains passwords, API keys, secrets
#   - If committed, anyone can see them!
#   - Different per environment (dev/prod)
#
# .env           → Main environment file
# .env.local     → Local overrides
# .env.*.local   → Environment-specific locals
#
# NEVER COMMIT THESE! Even if you delete them later,
# Git history keeps them forever!
#
# IF YOU ACCIDENTALLY COMMIT:
#   1. Change ALL passwords/secrets immediately
#   2. Use git-filter-repo to remove from history
#   3. Force push (coordinate with team!)
# ============================================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ============================================================================
# IDE / EDITOR
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Editor configuration and cache files
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Personal preference (everyone uses different editors)
#   - Can contain absolute paths
#   - Not needed for project to work
#
# .vscode/       → VS Code settings
# .idea/         → JetBrains (WebStorm, IntelliJ)
# *.swp, *.swo   → Vim swap files
# ============================================================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ============================================================================
# OPERATING SYSTEM
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: OS-generated files
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Not related to project
#   - Annoying in git status
#   - Different per OS
#
# .DS_Store      → macOS folder metadata
# Thumbs.db      → Windows thumbnail cache
# ============================================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ============================================================================
# LOGS
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Log files generated during development/runtime
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Can be huge
#   - Contains timestamps (always changing)
#   - Not needed in repository
#   - Might contain sensitive info
# ============================================================================
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# ============================================================================
# TESTING
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Test output and coverage reports
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Generated files
#   - Different every time you run tests
#   - Large coverage reports
# ============================================================================
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# ============================================================================
# USER UPLOADS
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Files uploaded by users (avatars, etc.)
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Can be huge
#   - User-specific data
#   - Different per environment
#   - Stored in Docker volumes anyway
# ============================================================================
uploads/
static/uploads/*
!static/uploads/.gitkeep
!static/uploads/avatars/
static/uploads/avatars/*
!static/uploads/avatars/.gitkeep

# ============================================================================
# DATABASE
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Local database files (if using SQLite for dev)
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Data changes constantly
#   - Binary files = bad for git
#   - Different per developer
#
# Note: We use PostgreSQL in Docker, but just in case!
# ============================================================================
*.db
*.db-journal
prisma/*.db
prisma/*.db-journal

# ============================================================================
# DOCKER
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Docker-related temporary files
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Generated by Docker
#   - Environment-specific
# ============================================================================
.docker/

# ============================================================================
# MISC
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: Other generated/temporary files
# WHY IGNORE: Various reasons - not needed in repo
#
# *.tgz          → npm pack output
# .cache/        → Various tool caches
# .turbo/        → Turborepo cache (if using)
# .vercel/       → Vercel deployment cache
# .output/       → Nitro output
# ============================================================================
*.tgz
.cache/
.turbo/
.vercel/
.output/

# ============================================================================
# CERTIFICATES (Local HTTPS)
# ============================================================================
# WHAT: SSL certificates for local development
# WHY IGNORE:
#   - Security: Private keys should never be committed
#   - Generated locally with mkcert or similar
#
# IF YOU NEED HTTPS LOCALLY:
#   Use mkcert: https://github.com/FiloSottile/mkcert
#   mkcert localhost
# ============================================================================
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.cert

# ============================================================================
# TIPS
# ============================================================================
#
# CHECK WHAT'S IGNORED:
#   git status --ignored
#
# SEE IF A FILE IS IGNORED:
#   git check-ignore -v <filename>
#
# FORCE ADD AN IGNORED FILE (not recommended):
#   git add -f <filename>
#
# STOP TRACKING A FILE (but keep locally):
#   git rm --cached <filename>
#
# ============================================================================

exp
